2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a unified planning paradigm that combines graph-based searches and sampling-based planners, which are both popular techniques in AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses advanced graph-search techniques and almost-surely asymptotically optimal sampling-based planners, which are both areas of machine learning. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses real-world problems and applications, which are relevant to the systems and control sub-category. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although not directly related to computer vision, the paper's focus on path planning and optimization could be relevant to certain computer vision applications, such as autonomous navigation.
